// A closure whose RESULT is an array of NULLABLE maps (`() => ({[string]: boolean} |
// null)[]`), reached through a struct FIELD and as a direct param / binding. The bare
// lambda `() => ([h1])` self-classified a NON-null `{[string]: boolean}[]` reflist keyed
// on a DIFFERENT `$fnsig` slot than the annotation-side value call's nullable-map
// `(…|null)[]` slot — divergent reflist tokens: a cast-failure TRAP (struct field) /
// "no interned signature" reject (direct param). Fixed by the nulMapElemListRetName
// adoption + recorder quadruple (`synthRetAnnots` pins via `parenUnionArrElemName`; the
// nullable-map sibling of nulStructElemListRetName). The named-fn value spelling and the
